  <prompt>
    Author `MatterMemoryPromotionService` (NEW) at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryPromotionService.cs` (+ interface `IMatterMemoryPromotionService` if not already authored by task 088) implementing the T2 → T3 user-approval promotion workflow per architecture §4.4 + §6.4 + §7.1. Three methods: `QueueForApprovalAsync(tenantId, matterId, sessionId, fact, source, confidence, ct)` writes a pending record to Cosmos `memory` container with doc-type `matter-memory-promotion` and id `promotion-pending_{guid}`; `ApproveAsync(promotionId, ct)` reads pending → calls existing `IMatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` → updates status to `approved`; `RejectAsync(promotionId, ct)` updates status to `rejected`. Dispatch of `memory.*` PaneEventBus events happens in task 096/097 (separate dispatch sites). Implements FR-32 (promotion workflow + Cosmos doc-type).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in Cosmos memory-container discriminator pattern + R6 MatterMemoryService reuse.</role>

  <goal>
    `MatterMemoryPromotionService` lives at `Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryPromotionService.cs` implementing `IMatterMemoryPromotionService`. Uses existing Cosmos `memory` container per architecture §7.1 (NO new container — discriminator pattern via `documentType` field). Writes/reads/updates pending records. Delegates the actual T3 durable write to existing `IMatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` on approve (architecture §4.3 wire-not-build). Unit tests cover Queue/Approve/Reject + race-condition handling (concurrent approve attempts → ETag) + ADR-015 telemetry safety (no fact text logged).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §3.2 rule 2 (T2 → T3 promotion is EXPLICIT), §4.4 (NEW service), §6.4 (promotion flow), §7.1 (Cosmos `memory` container; doc-type discriminator). The architectural rule is binding: this service is the ONLY path from T2 to T3; T2 → T3 NEVER auto-promotes; user approval is mediated via this service. The actual T3 write reuses existing `MatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` (architecture §4.3 — wire-not-build).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/IMatterMemoryService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceStateService.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No endpoint added here (tasks 094, 095 add endpoints).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Register concrete service in AiModule (already wired by task 091 if interface stub from task 088 was used; if task 088 created the stub, this task replaces it with concrete and updates DI accordingly).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service in `Services/Ai/Memory/` — BFF-internal. No PublicContracts facade required for chat-internal memory plumbing. `IMatterMemoryService` injection is allowed (cousin memory service).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry payload: serviceName + tenantId + matterId (boolean present/absent) + sessionId (deterministic ID) + promotionId (deterministic GUID) + status discriminator + durationMs ONLY. NEVER fact text, source text.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">≤+0.2 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§3.2 rule 2 — T2 → T3 mediation is explicit. `QueueForApprovalAsync` MUST NOT call `IMatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync`. `ApproveAsync` is the ONLY site that does so.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§7.1 — doc-type discriminator pattern: id format `promotion-pending_{guid}`, `documentType: "matter-memory-promotion"`. Partition `/tenantId`. 90d TTL inherits from container default.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§6.4 — schema of pending record matches: `{ id, documentType, tenantId, matterId, sessionId, fact, source, confidence, createdAt, status: "pending_approval" | "approved" | "rejected" }`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Concurrency: use Cosmos ETag (`IfMatch`) on Approve/Reject to detect duplicate processing.</constraint>
  </constraints>

